ABSTRACT
An integrated WLAN/WWAN architecture is described, in
which signaling used to control the integration of the
WLAN/WWAN architecture is performed over the Radio
Resource Control ("RRC”) plane. The integrated architec-
ture may provide a network-controlled framework for per-
forming traffic steering and radio resource management.
Additionally, according to the disclosure provided herein,
the integrated architecture may interwork with legacy sys-
tems (e.g., architectures that do not support the integrated
WLAN/WWAN architecture).
